China has become one of the busiest countries in the world in the field of transportation, a transport official said Friday. Over the last decade, the country has seen its key transport indicators, including passenger and freight railway, road, waterway and civil aviation volume; cargo throughput of ports; and business postal and express services volume rank top in the world, Vice Minister of Transport Xu Chengguang said at a media briefing. In 2021, ports on average reported over 69,000 ship entries and exits, while airports saw some 26,800 take-offs and landings every day, Xu added. In the peak traveling season, passenger trains make more than 10,000 trips and in 2021, expressways saw more than 60 million trips on average per day, the vice minister said. China's ministries started a series of media briefings in April, introducing the country's progress made in different sectors in the past decade.